 theory, concludes with an analysis of their effectiveness and ability to shock the viewer and create a citizen who is ready to take action against trafficking. The book seeks to explain why, despite the attention to the problem, communities continue to grapple with indifference, denial, and turning a blind eye to the existence of trafficking. Screening Trafficking: Prudent and Perilous offers fresh insights to readers interested in human trafficking and its representations as well as policymakers who are invested in well-informed decisions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aHuman trafficking in motion pictures. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  a21st century, Balkan, East and West, Film, Gender studies, Human trafficking, Media.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCentral European University Press eBook-Package 2018z978311078052940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789633862131423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789633862131/original  a978-3-11-078052-9  Central European University Press eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles